      "text": "10 Krey Boulevard, Rensselaer, NY 12144\nPh: 518.356.6000 | Fax: 518.356.8899\nWebsite: www.nyiso.com | LinkedIn: NYISO | Twitter: @NewYorkISO\nIMPORTANT NOTICE – TRANSITION CLUSTER STUDY PROCESS\nJuly 1, 2024\nRe: Notice of the Transition Cluster Study Application Window \nDear Stakeholders: \nThe Application Window for the Transition Cluster Study Process will open on August 1, 2024\nat 8am EDT. The closing date of the Transition Cluster Study Application Window will be on \nOctober 15, 2024 at 5pm EDT.\nPursuant to Section 40.5.4 of Attachment HH to the NYISO OATT, in order to become eligible to \nenter the Transition Cluster Study, an Interconnection Customer must submit and satisfy the \napplication requirements for either: \n(1) an Interconnection Request via NYISO Interconnection Projects Portal, \nhttps://nyiso.my.site.com/Interconnection/s/login/, or \n(2) a CRIS-Only Request, https://www.nyiso.com/documents/20142/1403912/CRIS\u0002Only-Request%20Form_fillable.pdf/b63a9da7-dfdc-bc55-46b4-8a2284945c1b, via email \nto InterconnectionSupport@nyiso.com.\nIn order to participate in the Transition Cluster Study Process, the Interconnection Customer\nmust provide all the required information during the Application Window, as described in Section \n40.5.5.1 of Attachment HH to the NYISO OATT. Failure to submit the application requirements \nby the close of the Application Window, which is October 15, 2024 at 5pm EDT, could result in \nwithdrawal and/or prevent the project from participating in the Transition Cluster Study. \nThe following items must be submitted during the Application Window:\n1. As applicable, must submit (i) a completed Interconnection Request including the \nrequired technical data, modeling and conceptual one-line project layout or (ii) a \ncompleted CRIS-Only Request;\n2. For a CRIS-Only Study Project, must provide documentation demonstrating that it is in\u0002service or has completed (i) a Class Year Study for ERIS, (ii) a completed facilities study \nfor Small Generating Facilities processed under the Small Generator Interconnection \nProcedures pursuant to Section 40.3.1 or (iii) a utility interconnection study if the facility \nis not subject to the NYISO interconnection procedures;\n3. Must submit a non-refundable Application Fee in cash in the amount of $10,000 for an \nInterconnection Request or $5,000 for a CRIS-Only Request;\n4. Must submit a Study Deposit, as applicable: \na. Based on the size of the proposed Facility: \ni. $100,000 for a Facility smaller than 80 MW, \nii. $150,000 for a Facility greater than or equal to 80 MW and smaller than \n200 MW, or \nPage 2\niii. $250,000 for a Facility greater than or equal to 200 MW for an \nInterconnection Request, or \nb. 50,000 for a CRIS-Only Request;\n5. Must demonstrate full Site Control of the Facility consistent with the acreage and other \nparameters for the Facility’s technology type including an attestation from the officer of \nthe company1;\n6. Must specify a single Point of Interconnection for the Interconnection Request, except (i) \nfor a Cluster Study Transmission Project or (ii) for a Generating Facility proposing to \ninterconnect at two Points of Interconnection within the same Capacity Region; and\n7. For an Interconnection Request for an inverter-based resource that is greater than 20 \nMW, must submit the attestation form required by NYSRC Reliability Rule B.52.\nIn addition, an Interconnection Customer must submit requests to be considered as an \nExcluded Facility, as well as Competitive Entry Exemption requests and Self-Supply Exemption \nrequests for the Transition Cluster Study to mma-icapmarketmitigation@nyiso.com and must be \nreceived by the NYISO no later than October 15, 2024 at 5pm EDT, which is the close of the \nApplication Window.\nIf you have any questions, please send an e-mail to InterconnectionSupport@nyiso.com. \n1 Links to (1) Technical Bulletin # 260 where information regarding Site Control requirements \nis described, https://www.nyiso.com/documents/20142/2931465/TB260-SiteControl\u0002v20240611-Final.pdf/e8a7bf3c-adf9-e5db-3a08-07fe258f4be4, (2) Minimum Acreage \nRequirement Met Attestation form, \nhttps://www.nyiso.com/documents/20142/1403912/Interconnection-Site-Control-Attestation\u0002Minimum-Acreage-Requirements-Met-fillable.pdf/5a5b2806-c929-181b-51b1-0a027841d113,\nand (3) Minimum Requirement Not Met Attestation form, \nhttps://www.nyiso.com/documents/20142/1403912/Interconnection-Customer-Site-Control\u0002Attestation-Minimum-Acreage-Requirements-Not-Met-fillable.pdf/1f61e343-bab5-1532-3ce4-\n458846d4d774.\n2 NYSRC Rule B.5 Compliance Attestation form, \nhttps://www.nyiso.com/documents/20142/1403912/NYSRC-Rule-B-5-Compliance\u0002Attestation-fillable.pdf/97162093-809e-ce45-a66e-3b412b0a44c5.",
